SIMPLE: infrequency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infrequency
<hw>In*fre"quen*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>infrequentia</ets>
scantiness : cf. F. <ets>infrequence</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state of rarely occuring; uncommonness; rareness; <as>as, the
<ex>infrequence</ex> of his visits</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of not being frequented; solitude;
isolation; retirement; seclusion.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The solitude and <qex>infrequency</qex> of the place.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infrequent</ent>⟦br⟧
